						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">commodorejohn wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The advantages I can think of that the NES has over the SMS are:<br />* Better support for hardware expansion (i.e. the sound-in pins on the Famicom)<br />* A significantly nicer sound chip<br />* The 6502 (I agree that the Z80 is just confusing)<br />* Slightly nicer sprite handling (flipping support)<br />Other than that, the SMS is generally the nicer machine.</div>
<br />
<br />1. Useless to us in the west.
<br />3. Purely a matter of opinion. Once you get used to the Z80, it's not that bad, and it's much more powerful.</div>

					
